The paper deals with the efficiency of game-theoretical algorithms in clustering large-sized data sets. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for selecting a subset of strategies from the strategies profile for each player, which could be related to the sub-category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of game theory in clustering could also be related to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the impact of time and game complexity on the efficiency of the algorithms, which could be related to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
